---
const pageTitle = "The Golden Gear";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
  </head>
      <body>
         <header class="project-hero">
                  <h1>{pageTitle}</h1>
                  <div class="project-meta">
                    <span><strong>Type:</strong> Video Game</span>
                    <span><strong>Timeline:</strong> 4 months</span>
                    <span><strong>Purpose:</strong> Skills USA</span>
                  </div>
                </header>

                <section class="description-box">
                    <p>
                    This video game was made by me and a teammate for the SkillsUSA Interactive Application
                    and Video Game development competition. It was made by a teammate and I in GameMaker Studio 2
                    where they did the art and music while I programmed and designed the levels. The game won regionals
                    which moved it to the state competition for California where it proceeded to win 1st place.
                    This game was coded in GML and taught me how to work with a team effectively, use GitHub,
                    create interesting level design, use collision circles for player interactions, and create simple enemy AI.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <figure class="screenshot-card">
                    <img src="/goldenGear/menuGG.png" alt="Menu" />
                        <figcaption>
                        The Golden Gear is a Steampunk Themed puzzle platformer that follows a narrative about the player
                        on a quest to find the rare Golden Gear to finish crafting their time machine. The player goes through
                        4 levels where they will need to interact with steam pipes and wheels to navigate the maze like locations.
                        </figcaption>
                </figure>

                <figure class="screenshot-card">
                    <img src="/goldenGear/mapGG.png" alt="Map" />
                        <figcaption>
                        A map was added to show each level to enhance the
                        idea of exploration and progress.
                        </figcaption>
                </figure>

                <figure class="screenshot-card">
                    <img src="/goldenGear/level1GG.png" alt="Level 1" />
                        <figcaption>
                        Level 1 Showcase. This level is in the main character's workshop
                        where the player can see the contraptions.
                        </figcaption>
                </figure>

                <figure class="screenshot-card">
                    <img src="/goldenGear/level2GG.png" alt="Level 2" />
                        <figcaption>
                        Level 2 Showcase. Level 2 starts outside the workshop
                        and opens into a large city of maze like pipe systems.
                        </figcaption>
                </figure>

                <figure class="multi-image-card">
                  <div class="image-group">
                    <img src="/goldenGear/enemy1GG.png" alt="Level 3 Enemy 1" />
                    <img src="/goldenGear/enemy2GG.png" alt="Level 3 Enemy 2" />
                  </div>
                        <figcaption>
                        Level 3 Showcase. Level 3 occurs on the airship docks
                        as the player proceeds to try and catch a ride on a flying boat
                        . Enemies called Time Snatchers are
                        introduced in the 3rd level. Contact with one will damage the
                        player acting as an extra obstacle.
                        </figcaption>
                  </figure>

                <figure class="screenshot-card">
                    <img src="/goldenGear/level4GG.png" alt="Level 4" />
                        <figcaption>
                        Level 4 Showcase. This level is on an airship and combines
                        the different quirks of each level.
                        </figcaption>
                </figure>

                <figure class="screenshot-card">
                    <img src="/goldenGear/hiddenGG.png" alt="Hidden Fairy" />
                        <figcaption>
                        Each level has a fairy which acts as a hidden collectable.
                        This gives incentive for the player to revisit past levels
                        and look closer.
                        </figcaption>
                </figure>

                <figure class="screenshot-card">
                    <img src="/goldenGear/codeGG.png" alt="Code" />
                        <figcaption>
                        Code Showcase.
                        </figcaption>
                </figure>

                    <footer class="bottom-nav">
                        <a href="/" class="home-button">Home</a>
                    </footer>
      </body>
</html>

<style>
.project-hero {
    background-color: #3D2B1F;
    border: 4px solid #D4AF37;
    border-radius: 16px;
    padding: 40px 20px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    text-align: center;
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2);
  }

.project-hero h1 {
    color: #D4AF37;
    font-size: 3rem;
    margin: 0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
  }

.project-meta {
    margin-top: 15px;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 20px;
    color: #D4AF37;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

.project-meta span {
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
    padding: 5px 15px;
    border-radius: 20px;
  }

.description-box {
    background-color: #262626;
    border: 4px solid #3f3f46;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 25px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #d1d5db;
  }

.description-box p {
    margin-bottom: 15px;
  }

body {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 20px;
    font-family: arial;
    background-color: #1a1a1a;
    color: #f3f4f6;
  }

.screenshot-card {
    background-color: #2d2d2d;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
    text-align: center;
  }

.screenshot-card img {
    max-width: 100%;
    border-radius: 8px;
    height: auto;
  }

.screenshot-card figcaption {
    margin-top: 15px;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #D4AF37;
  }

.multi-image-card {
    background-color: #2d2d2d;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
  }

.image-group {
    display: flex;
    gap: 10px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
  }

.image-group img {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 300px;
    max-width: 48%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

figcaption {
    margin-top: 15px;
    text-align: center;
    color: #D4AF37;
    font-style: italic;
  }

.bottom-nav {
    margin-top: 60px;
    padding: 40px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid #374151;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

a {
    color: #4f46e5;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: bold;
  }

.home-button {
    display: inline-block;
    background-color: #B87333;
    color: white;
    padding: 16px 32px;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 50px;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(184, 115, 51, 0.4);
  }

.home-button:hover {
    background-color: #B87333;
    transform: translateY(-3px);
    box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(184, 115, 51, 0.6);
  }
</style>